Before I left @onsiteworkshops in December of last year, I was given the advice to take a year off of the things that I believed may be holding me back, and to see where I was a year later. These photos serve as living proof that when you put in the work, you get the results. November 2022 was the month where I bought my first home (and farm), celebrated musical milestones with more of the country music legends I grew up listening to, began my DIY renovations, spent cherished time with new friends and family, made June a titans fan, and had some pretty cool musical milestones of my own. Feeling intensely grateful for all of the blessings and people in my life in this season and all the ones that led up to it. Lord bless you all, and may peace carry you into this holiday season. - J

1 year // I haven’t posted a single thing about this throughout the past 12 months because when I started this journey, I decided it was between God and I. He was the one who told me that I could do it, and just like He always is, He was right. I didn’t want to make my recovery process about incrementally highlighting it on social media (please note that if you yourself are in recovery and your own process consists of doing so, then that is absolutely wonderful and I encourage you to go about making it work in any and every way that you can!). Just the other day, when I celebrated one year of sobriety, I felt like it was the right time to share this milestone in hopes that it will help just one more person. The chip in this picture is something that I decided to go and pick up as a token to further commemorate one of the best years, if not the single best year of my entire life. I want you all to know what whatever struggles you face in your life, you can prevail. And that there is always somebody who loves you waiting to help 🤍

Happy 3rd Birthday June! I bought you a farm 🎁

40:31 • A story about Patience

On December 1, 2021, I wrote a word to start my journal for the coming year. That word was “Patience”. It would be my word to pray into and to work on, to discover in myself and uncover in the world around me. As many of y’all know, I received the blessing of being able to put down some roots towards the end of last year and buy a home, a farmhouse on a ranch beyond my wildest of dreams…but like all good things in life, that too did not come without its own rollercoaster ride of ups and downs.

After nearly a year of searching for the right home and placing endless declined offers on countless properties, I essentially gave up on the search after losing the house I truly believed to be “the one”. It was at this point I remembered my word “patience”, and so I took a step back and decided to give it to God and let Him do what He does. Sure enough, a few months later I randomly came across a property on my own that had every single thing I had been looking for. “How has this house not sold?” I asked myself, and so I decided to take a leap of faith and give it one more shot and put in an offer. Sure enough, it was accepted. 

Every single part of the process of acquiring the home came so incredibly easy, and so on the day I learned that it would close, I had a thought, “where does the address appear in the Bible?”. I googled “4031”….

Isaiah 40:31 - “Those who wait on the Lord….”

Amen.
•
#patience #faith #isaiah4031

My Testimony
•
I was baptized one year ago today on January 23 of 2022 surrounded by my friends and family at @crosspoint.tv. I had heard things like “watch how God will start to move in your new life”, and “get ready for the blessings about to come your way”. I had absolutely no clue how miraculously true that statement was, and how much power there was in what He was about to do with my life.
•
The incredible team at crosspoint asked me to share my testimony with the church, and on my one year anniversary of walking with Jesus, I wanted to share it with you. It is a deeply personal video and incredibly important for me to share because without a single doubt, this past year has been the most blessed of my life, and every time I see this video, it reminds me exactly with whom the glory truly lies. What a great father He is.
•
Thank you to everyone at @crosspoint.tv for the love and the community you constantly create and for helping me share my story with others.
•
#testimony #mystory #praisegod

A Move Of God… #april 
•
This time last year I was about to play my set at stagecoach, and at that time I truly believed that there was no greater stage I could ever stand on and sing from…

Spending these last few months leaning into leading worship for the first time in my life, both in and out of the church, I have come to believe a greater truth, in that every stage I have stood on up to this point in my life has only been but a training ground preparing me for the most important stage of all. I believe it is no coincidence that this new stage comes with both the most responsibility, and also the greatest reward. It is the stage where I get to use the gifts God has so graciously bestowed upon me and give them right back to Him by ushering His glory and presence into the room. This is the stage that feels the most like home.

And this all goes so much further than just music or leading worship.

We are all capable of bringing the spirit of God with us wherever we go. We can all be beacons of light brightening the lives of all those we come in contact with.

In the words of @kevinqueen…”looking a little more like love, is looking a lot more like Jesus”.
Happiness is not a station you arrive at, but a manner of traveling… #may

The absolute legend and very good friend of ours, Jesse Labelle (@jesselabellemusic), hopped on the podcast and shared exactly what we needed to hear. If you haven’t gotten to know Jesse yet, he’s a music artist and songwriter building his dreams from Nashville, TN. ⁣
⁣
With more than enough stories to write a book (that would for sure turn into a Netflix series), Jesse has experienced just about every kind of obstacle you can imagine. No matter what seemingly impossible odds he’s faced, Jesse has always found a way forward through faith. ⁣
⁣
In our convo, Jesse shares how there’s purpose in the process, how to find meaning in the moment, and how God uses everything you’ve gone through as preparation for all that’s ahead. ⁣

MUSIC MINISTRY 🎸🙏 // October 23-27 in San Luis + Mesa Rica with @thealoefamily 
•
Music ministry has been a part of my life from the moment I picked up a guitar. In the beginning, it was music itself that ministered to me by bringing me the joy and allowing me to find the comfort and companionship I struggled to find elsewhere. Throughout the years as a life in music began to write itself into my story, I began to see how I might be able to take that same joy and comfort music had brought to me, and share it with others.  From Canada to Kenya to Nashville, I’ve been blessed to serve with some of the most wonderful organizations and in October, thanks to The Aloe Family, I get to add Mexico to that list. We are looking for musical volunteers to join us and you can see all of the details at www.thealoefamily.com/international skills teaching-trips/

The times in my life where I feel that I have stood the closest to God have always been when I have taken the time to pour into the opportunity and receive the blessing of using my time to support and serve others.
•
Last week in Mexico with @thealoefamily, my eyes and my heart were opened wide while living in the presence of circumstances beyond the comprehension of the daily life I myself, and so many others I know, lead. This is what perspective is all about, and I urge anyone with a heart for understanding and for healing, whether for yourself, for others, or both, to pour into the community of those in need around you, and if you are so blessed to have the chance, into a community abroad. 
•
Thank you to The Aloe Family, to Natalie, Madison, Moncell, Mario, Luis, Peña, Brandon, Omar and everyone who shared their smile and their kind heart for this experience and for beginning relationships, and starting a mission that I look forward to continuing, supporting, moving forward and completing. Much Love - J

“What A Beautiful Name”
•
⁣Whats in a name?⠀
⠀
What is a name outside of the grouping of letters we use to identify each other?⠀
⠀
A name can be more than just the sound of alphabetical symbols strung together.⠀
⠀
Throughout history there have been many names associated with God.⠀
⠀
Emmanuel - God is with us.⠀
⠀
Adonai - Lord or master.⠀
⠀
El Shaddai - Lord God almighty.⠀
⠀
But God gave Himself a name in the book of Exodus, that name was Yaweh/Jahweh which is translated into I am.⠀
⠀
Did you know that when you sing Hallelujah, the Jah is really the Jah in Jahweh.⠀
⠀
So it’s Hallelu = Praise be to + Jah = God. Hallelujah = Praise God.⠀
⠀
You also see that piece of Gods name in another name. That name Jah becomes the J in Jesus. Sus means salvation or saves.⠀
⠀
So Jesus names literally means God Saves. Thats part of what makes His name so great.⠀
⠀
It’s the name God chose for Himself put into action.⠀
⠀
It’s the name that can bring healing and break down walls.⠀
⠀
It’s the name that brings beauty from ashes and causes dead, dry bones to come to life.⠀
⠀
And it’s the name of our savior king who came down from heaven to be near each one of us.⠀
⠀
It’s the name that’s worthy of all our praise.⠀
⠀
Jesus.

Christmas at Crosspoint // 12.21.23 🕯️
•
Last night I witnessed the miracle of Christmas for the first time.
•
Last Christmas in 2022 was my first year as a believer and was to be the first time I’d attend church on Christmas knowing what it means to celebrate to birth of the savior of the world. Last Christmas however, an ice storm hit Tennessee and roads were closed all across Nashville leaving me with the only option of staying home and watching the recorded service online. (I actually still drove to church in the hopes there were some people there who’d have braved the snow having some sort of service. That’s how badly I wanted to spend Christmas in the same room I’d been baptized in 11 months earlier).
•
Fast forward to 2023, a year of devoting so much more time to praying with our church, doing a deeper dive into scripture and finishing reading the Bible for the first time! A year where I learned the true meaning of what it means to worship.
•
To be in that room last night and watch the church exude and share the light that has turned my life around literally led me to tears in the middle of the candlelit service during “Silent Night”. I will never ever forget it. 
•
Passing along SO MUCH love and gratitude to my church family and everyone on the team with @crosspointmusicofficial, the incredibly talented and hard working creative team @crosspointcrtv, Our pastor @kevinqueen, and every single person at @crosspoint.tv last night and every week. You’ve all shown me what light looks like and what life is really all about. 
•
And a very special shoutout to our worship pastors @cheryl_stark and @dwanhill who lead the leaders pouring so much heart and guidance into this team, the church, and into all of our lives.
•
Merry Christmas y’all!!!
•
#christmas #christmaseve #church #worship #worshipleader #jesus #joy #hope #light #gratitude #love #holy #silentnight

Hi 👋 My name is Jesse Labelle.
•
I have made a handful of records in many different genres of music and if you’re here because one of those songs or albums has played a part of your life, welcome back!
•
If you’re new here, I am also a worship leader, in of whom God has been doing a great work. These days, I find myself singing a whole lot about my faith in Him.
•
